HEADWORD: Septuagesima
<hw>Sep`tu*a*ges"i*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>septuagesimus</ets> the seventieth, fr.
<ets>septuaginta</ets> seventy.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The third
Sunday before Lent; -- so called because it is about seventy days before
Easter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

